<br>
Give everyone what they want, and then give the ones that are SUPPOSED to be above them, more!<br>
<br>
If the druids want a, b, c, d, etc, then do it.  But then improve wizards dramatically.  I have no problems making them the absolute Kings (and Queens) of DD, and damage per mana.  Make them have fast-cast, lower dmg spells, and extreme damage, slower-casting, all with high dmg/mana ratios.  Let them have good DDs vs most of the elements, and good AE.  Wizards should never really even be able to be APPROACHED for damage, let alone side-by-side, or marginally better.<br>
<br>
Then, make Magicians #2.  We were always intended this way.  Our pets are the substitute for not having roots, snares, Shieldskin, etc.  They are our taunter so we can nuke away.  They also do major damage.  That's why we are #2.  At the end of the fight, a Wizard and a Mage should have similar damage output, but with a Wizard it is ALL in DD or AE, while the magician supplements his/her slightly lower dmg output with the pet, and gains the agro and taunt advantages.  Druids should not even be in the same league.  Don't hit any classes with nerfs, just make each class fufill the role intended.  Wizards #1 nukers in dmg/second, and most efficiant DDs.  Magicians #2.  Necros, Shamans, and Druids for DoTs, while more mana efficiant, do not take down a mob in the same time.  Druids should probably be after Magicians in Nuking power, with Enchanters or Shamans after them.  Clerics should not even approach any of these classes.  Why give the class with the BEST heals in the game, and an undeniably secure spot at ANY point in the game the ability to be a great nuker as well?<br>
<br>
